This paper deals with OCR (Optical Character Recognition) for historical printings, which involves text recognition and language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Deep Learning (cs.DL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
